types.documentation:

only should go to a single receiver. If multiple workers are listening
to a queue only one of them will be called with the task.

properties.name: enqueue
properties.documentation: Put data on the queue

properties.name: process
properties.documentation:
Process work on a queue. fn will be called with the data added to the queue.

If the worker returns a promise, it will be awaited before a new
task is pulled from the queue.

properties.name: publish
properties.documentation: Publish data on the channel

properties.name: subscribe
properties.documentation: Subscribes to channel, fn will be called with the published data for all messages/

properties.name: provide
properties.documentation:
Provides/makes an rpc function avalible to call.
fn will be called with the args passed to request and the returned data
will be returned in request

properties.name: request
properties.documentation: Calls an RPC function

properties.name: labels
properties.documentation:
The labels assigned to the event, this is similar to the bucketName in the UI
An event can be assigned multiple labels for example to support multiple granularities.

Example for a Facebook reaction: ["reaction-wow", "reactions-positive", "reactions"]

properties.name: timestamp
properties.documentation: Timestamp in milliseconds

properties.name: value
properties.documentation: Any value for this event, usually something like a number in a graph

properties.name: properties
properties.documentation: Properties that is  filtered on, for example pageId and companyId

properties.name: metadata
properties.documentation: Extra metadata, for example an error event might include browser and os versions here

properties.name: since
properties.documentation: Timestamp in milliseconds

properties.name: until
properties.documentation: Timestamp in milliseconds

properties.name: period
properties.documentation:
A global period of events to fetch, will be overriden if the bucket Query
specifices a period

properties.name: limit
properties.documentation:
A global limit of events per bucket, will be overriden if the bucket Query
specifices a limit

properties.name: filter
properties.documentation:
A global filter to match the properties of an event, for example:
`{pageId: 'uuid'}`

properties.name: store
properties.documentation: A redux store

properties.name: tokenPath
properties.documentation: Path in the store where an authentication token is placed

properties.name: url
properties.documentation: The url to query

properties.name: abort
properties.documentation: If true the query will be aborted if there already is another query running

properties.name: clear
properties.documentation: If true the bucket is overwritten with the new bucket, otherwise the bucket is merged

properties.name: replace
properties.documentation:
If true all other buckets in the reducer will be removed otherwise
they will be merged and buckets that existed and did exist in the
response will be overwriten

properties.name: query
properties.documentation:
Run a query to fetch buckets. The response will be dispatched as an redux
action so that the buckets reducer is updated

variables.name: actions
variables.value:
createActions({
  setBucket: {} as Action<{name: string, bucket: Bucket}>,
  replaceBuckets: {} as Action<BucketCollection>,
  clearAllBuckets: {} as Action<{}>,
  markLoading: {} as Action<{bucketNames: Array<string>, replace: boolean, clear: boolean}>,
  setError: {} as Action<{bucketNames: Array<string>, error: any, replace: boolean, clear: boolean}>,
})

properties.name: name
properties.documentation: Name for the RPC namespace, if not specified the classname will be used.

properties.name: rpcObjects
properties.documentation:
Optional id to use when handling multiple RPC servers on a single WebSocketServer.
The same id must be specified on the client.
